  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 ; \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "It is dangerous to talk about the division of plantation lands in the face of political instability; Velu Kumar",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Velu Kumar, the Kandy district parliamentarian of the Tamil Progressive Alliance, said it was dangerous to talk about the division of plantations in the face of political instability.",
        "Today, it is unclear who owns the government, whose leadership and control of the government and the state administration.",
        "The President is in the bunker trying to advance his agenda. The Prime Minister is in the process of advancing his party's agenda by including his party colleagues. In such a political instability it is dangerous to talk about the division of plantation lands.",
        "Today there is no democratically elected government in the country. The people's representatives are nominally subject to the clutches of some. Ranil Wickremesinghe is the only Prime Minister who has only one seat in Parliament. Rejected by the people, he has been carrying out his work projects highlighting some of his party colleagues. In such a situation the people's representatives are on the sidelines. We, the opposition, boycotted parliament last week to point this out.",
        "Uncultivated plantation lands in hilly areas have been a topic of discussion for a long time. The issue is being discussed again with the food famine in the country today.",
        "Plantation people have been discriminated against in the distribution of plantation lands throughout the past. As in all areas, large tracts of land have been allotted to outsiders.",
        "In this situation there are no upcountry representatives in the present government. Some who were there claim to have become independent. It is also questionable who owns the state leadership. Talking about the division of plantation lands in this situation would be like betraying ourselves.",
        "The present government has not been able to carry out any development work. Government representatives at the district level have the opportunity to use this to the satisfaction of their colleagues.",
        "Currently, the government has made arrangements to give away large tracts of land in the Kalapoda Estate, Del Thottai Estate, Bohil Estate and Great Outer Estate in the Kandy District. There is also a lot of controversy surrounding the land acquisition of Woodside Gardens and Calduria Gardens.",
        "We have to stop all this, protect the plantation lands and provide them for the livelihood of the plantation people. Apart from that, in today's weak political environment, the division of plantation lands will be an opportunity to fulfill the agendas of the majority political representatives. Let's talk about plans and make decisions from Colombo.",
        "But, when they come into operation at the divisional level, various nuisances arise as party organizers, MPs, government officials. Despite all that, there is no environment today that can provide plantation lands for the plantation people to cultivate.",
        "Today a special relief program should be launched to protect the plantation people. That is what we must emphasize. Rather speaking of uncultivated land, we are looking for danger ourselves."
      ],
